data.description: ** VA Loan Assumption Possible for Qualifying Buyers! **Nestled at the end of College St with pretty views of neighboring farm fields and a hilltop vineyard in the distance, this charming home offers nearly 1300 square feet, 3 bedrooms, and 2 bathrooms.Step inside to discover a cozy atmosphere with plenty of natural light throughout. The primary bedroom is generously sized, with a large closet and ensuite bathroom featuring dual sinks, a tile-surround shower, and freestanding soaking tub. The spacious living areas are perfect for relaxation or gatherings, while the kitchen is equipped with an oversized sink, dishwasher, refrigerator, electric range, and overhead microwave. The laundry room includes a washer and dryer, while offering substantial pantry storage space and shelving.Freshly painted this fall, the exterior of the home is complemented by established trees, shrubs, and flowers that add a touch of natural beauty throughout the year. Gardening enthusiasts will appreciate the tool shed for storing supplies. A large rear concrete patio, complete with a hot tub, offers a haven for relaxation and beautiful views of the night sky. Whether you're unwinding after a long day or hosting friends and family, this outdoor space is a versatile retreat. Bring your toys as this property offers extra parking, too!Located within a historic and welcoming community, Echo is home to a prized school district, the 2023 1A State Champion Football team, wineries, shops, a beautiful golf course, and more. Now's your chance to call Echo home - contact your favorite agent to schedule a private tour today!
